we’re all familiar with —&nbsp;joy, warmth, fear;

00:15:42.880 --> 00:15:48.240
others claim that the defining feature of
the sensation is that it’s impossible to describe.

00:15:48.240 --> 00:15:52.820
A sensation can’t be both possible and impossible to describe.

00:15:52.820 --> 00:15:57.640
Some folks present divine love as 
one specific, distinctive type of sensation;

00:15:57.640 --> 00:16:02.340
others suggest divine love can be experienced 
in completely different ways by different people.

00:16:02.340 --> 00:16:07.940
A sensation can’t be both one distinctive
sensation and many unrelated sensations.

00:16:07.940 --> 00:16:12.300
These contradictions demonstrate that at least
some of these people must be wrong.

00:16:12.300 --> 00:16:17.600
Which in turn demonstrates that it’s perfectly
possible to believe divine love is unmistakable

00:16:17.600 --> 00:16:20.560
—&nbsp;and yet be mistaken.

00:16:20.560 --> 00:16:23.580
The major religions have us chasing ‘divine love’

00:16:23.580 --> 00:16:28.000
in arbitrary life events and 
arbitrary physical sensations.

00:16:28.000 --> 00:16:31.140
We might as well be chasing clouds.

00:16:38.700 --> 00:16:43.280
In many species, the offspring’s survival 
will hinge on it’s parents’ protection.

00:16:43.280 --> 00:16:48.260
In these cases, the bond between parent and offspring 
is predictably extremely intense.

00:16:48.260 --> 00:16:52.100
Parents develop muscularly 
protective instincts towards their offspring.

00:16:52.100 --> 00:16:57.060
And offspring develop equally muscular 
trusting instincts towards their parents.

00:16:57.060 --> 00:17:02.180
But sometimes, this bond gets hijacked 
by other species for their own purposes.

00:17:02.180 --> 00:17:03.900
The cuckoo is a ‘brood parasite’

00:17:03.900 --> 00:17:07.700
that exploits the parental instincts 
of other species like reed warblers

00:17:07.700 --> 00:17:12.800
by laying its own eggs in the their nests, fooling them into treating the young cuckoo as their own.

00:17:12.800 --> 00:17:17.220
When it hatches, the cuckoo is hardwired to push all the other eggs out of the nest

00:17:17.220 --> 00:17:22.380
so that the adopted parent can focus exclusively on feeding its mammoth appetite.

00:17:22.380 --> 00:17:27.300
A reverse example, where a false parent 
is introduced, is seen with the goose.

00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:29.960
Within the first few hours of hatching from their egg

00:17:29.960 --> 00:17:33.340
baby geese will bond with 
the first suitable object they experience

00:17:33.340 --> 00:17:37.180
and then follow that object over land, water and air.

00:17:37.180 --> 00:17:40.600
In the wild, this first object will generally be their parent.

00:17:40.600 --> 00:17:44.180
But many humans have exploited 
this process, known as ‘imprinting’

00:17:44.180 --> 00:17:47.480
to gain amazing video footage of geese in flight

00:17:47.480 --> 00:17:50.380
by establishing themselves as that first object

00:17:50.380 --> 00:17:56.240
so that when they later take to a speedboat
or hang-glider, the imprinted geese will follow.

00:17:56.240 --> 00:18:00.520
Human children are dependent on their parents
for an unusually long developmental period

00:18:00.520 --> 00:18:02.240
compared to other species.

00:18:02.240 --> 00:18:06.540
Typically, they’ll display an 
unquestioning trust and submissiveness

00:18:06.540 --> 00:18:08.760
to their parents for a significant part 
of that development.

00:18:08.760 --> 00:18:11.720
In theory, this should a good survival strategy

00:18:11.720 --> 00:18:16.740
because their parents are likely to be the most fiercely protective adults in those formative years.

00:18:16.740 --> 00:18:22.020
To mistrust or resist their parents at that early stage might actively endanger them.

00:18:22.020 --> 00:18:26.500
But sometimes, these survival instincts 
are hijacked for other purposes

00:18:26.500 --> 00:18:29.880
—&nbsp;not by other species, but by ideologies.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:33.360
Religions such as the various branches of
Christianity and Islam

00:18:33.360 --> 00:18:37.360
attempt to introduce a false father in the
form of an invisible god

00:18:37.360 --> 00:18:41.500
— a parasitic parent that 
will divert and endlessly exploit

00:18:41.500 --> 00:18:44.560
the child’s natural instincts trust and submission.

00:18:44.560 --> 00:18:47.420
In healthy human parent-child relationships

00:18:47.420 --> 00:18:51.740
the growing child develops into 
an independent, self-reliant adult.

00:18:51.740 --> 00:18:57.100
Unquestioning trust and submission resolve
into healthy challenge and mutual respect.

00:18:57.100 --> 00:19:00.080
Parental hypocrisies are acknowledged and recede.

00:19:00.090 --> 00:19:02.670
But in the parasitic god relationship

00:19:02.670 --> 00:19:07.160
the growing child becomes fixed 
in an undeveloped infantilised stage

00:19:07.160 --> 00:19:10.760
remaining psychologically stunted in a child’s mindset

00:19:10.770 --> 00:19:15.840
Unquestioning trust and submission are 
perpetually demanded under threat of punishment.

00:19:15.840 --> 00:19:19.220
Parental hypocrisies are denied and continue.

00:19:19.220 --> 00:19:21.660
But the most striking difference is this:

00:19:21.660 --> 00:19:28.500
In healthy human-child relationships, the parent 
gives relentless demonstrations of love to the child

00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:37.360
— actively protecting, affirming, reassuring,
empathising, nurturing and teaching.

00:19:37.360 --> 00:19:43.700
In the parasitic god relationship, the parent demands relentless demonstrations of love from the child

00:19:43.700 --> 00:19:48.120
requiring constant declarations and acts of devotion.

00:19:48.120 --> 00:19:52.240
In fact, with this role reversal 
of the child feeding the parent

00:19:52.240 --> 00:19:56.020
the parasite that gods 
most closely resemble is the cuckoo.

00:19:56.020 --> 00:19:59.100
The baby bird with the ever-open beak.

00:19:59.100 --> 00:20:04.420
While these cuckoos don’t themselves have
the ability to kill —&nbsp;being mythical characters —

00:20:04.420 --> 00:20:09.920
stories in the Bible and Qur’an such as
Abraham’s instruction to sacrifice his own son

00:20:09.920 --> 00:20:16.460
depict both Yahweh and Allah desiring to have family members ready to kill each other on command.

00:20:16.460 --> 00:20:21.340
What kind of loving parents want their families
ready to kill each other?

00:20:21.340 --> 00:20:23.880
This should be the point where families wake up

00:20:23.880 --> 00:20:27.620
and see that they’ve been taken over by
something extremely malignant.

00:20:27.620 --> 00:20:30.680
But the cuckoo works 
to separate them from each other.

00:20:30.680 --> 00:20:35.980
We come back to Al-Ghazali’s commentary,
and the curious concept of making a servant ‘sincere’.

00:20:35.980 --> 00:20:37.540
What’s meant by this is that

00:20:37.540 --> 00:20:40.600
‘God does not leave for him his family and property ....

00:20:40.600 --> 00:20:42.360
‘He makes him separate from others

00:20:42.360 --> 00:20:46.160
‘and God comes in between him
and other people and things.’

00:20:46.160 --> 00:20:50.120
And apparently gods aren’t the only ones 
seeking to come between family members.

00:20:50.120 --> 00:20:54.580
Within Islam, the Hadith is&nbsp;a collection of books 
written long after the death of Muhammad

00:20:54.580 --> 00:20:58.000
— the self-proclaimed messenger of the Islamic god, Allah.

00:20:58.000 --> 00:21:02.400
The Hadith gathers together reports 
of Muhammad’s life from various sources.

00:21:02.400 --> 00:21:04.940
These have been subdivided by Islamic scholars

00:21:04.940 --> 00:21:10.180
into classifications of 
authentic, good, weak or fabricated.

00:21:10.180 --> 00:21:14.660
In one passage considered authentic, 
Muhammad is reported to have said:

00:21:14.660 --> 00:21:21.720
‘None of you is a believer till I am dearer to him than 
his child, his father and the whole of mankind.’

00:21:21.720 --> 00:21:29.120
This stupendous egotism is eerily echoed by the Christian messiah Jesus in Matthew 10:37:

00:21:29.120 --> 00:21:33.860
‘Anyone who loves their father or mother 
more than me is not worthy of me;

00:21:33.860 --> 00:21:38.220
‘anyone who loves their son or daughter
more than me is not worthy of me.’

00:21:38.220 --> 00:21:43.100
So we have Allah, Yahweh, Muhammad and Jesus

00:21:43.100 --> 00:21:47.220
all demanding supremacy over 
every other human relationship.

00:21:47.220 --> 00:21:51.620
And we all know the punishments supposedly
awaiting those who don’t comply.

00:21:51.620 --> 00:21:56.940
Forget ‘hate speech’. For me, this is
the most dangerous kind of language

00:21:56.940 --> 00:22:02.060
— the language of totalitarian ultimatums,
that seeks to conquer by dividing,

00:22:02.060 --> 00:22:08.620
trying to come between us and our loved ones
in order to achieve total subservience.

00:22:08.620 --> 00:22:11.520
My love isn’t to be had for the asking.

00:22:11.520 --> 00:22:17.740
My love isn’t to be had on the promise of a gift 
that gives nothing but takes endlessly.

00:22:17.740 --> 00:22:24.840
And my love certainly isn’t to be had 
by anyone who attempts to dictate who I love.

00:22:24.840 --> 00:22:28.100
In part two, I’ll be continuing my exploration,

00:22:28.100 --> 00:22:33.200
looking at slave mentality, at sacrifice, at shunning

00:22:33.200 --> 00:22:38.400
and at the process of healing from this degrading love.

